{{Infobox person |name = Doug Chappel |other names = Doug Chappel Jr |image = Comedian Doug Chappel.jpg |caption = Doug Chappel |birth_place = [[Melbourne, Victoria]], [[Australia]]}} '''Doug Chappel''' is an [[Australia]]n [[comedian]] who grew up in the working class suburbs of [[Footscray, Victoria|Footscray]] and [[Sunshine]] in [[Melbourne|Melbourne's]] Western [[Suburb]]s. Chappel is also known for his work in the community with homeless youth & troubled teenagers. Once homeless himself and growing up with a "rough crowd", Chappel draws on his experiences from his past and applies it to his comedy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.standup.com.au/comedian/doug-chappel |title=Doug Chappel &#124; The Sit Down Comedy Club |publisher=Standup.com.au |date= |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref><ref>http://www.dougchappel.com{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>http://www.maroondah-leader.whereilive.com.au/.../it-helps-if-you-can-laugh/{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
In 2016 it was announced that Doug Chappel would be the new Ambassador for the Salvation Army's Westcare lead tenant program as a result of his continued support of the Western Suburbs, and his dedication and commitment to helping disadvantaged youth.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salvationarmy.org.au/en/Find-Us/Victoria/Westcare/Our-Services/Transitional-Services/Lead-Tenant-Program/ |title=Lead Tenant Program |publisher=Salvationarmy.org.au |date= |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref>
Doug Chappel is known as a versatile performer with shows ranging from performing for the Prime Minister of Australian and other political leaders, to hosting the Australian Adult Industry Awards and Sexpo. Chappel's brand of comedy has been described as "uniquely hilarious" and "charismatic", with appearance on NBC in Los Angeles, the London Comedy Store and he has entertained the troops for the [[Australian Defence Force]] in countries such as, Afghanistan, Dubai, Solomon Islands and East Timor. Chappel has also had sold out Melbourne International Comedy Festival shows in 2004, 2005, 2006, 2007 and 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.speakersandevents.com.au/directory/8601 |title=A Positive Move |publisher=Speakers and Events |date= |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref><ref name="corporatecomedians1">{{cite web|url=http://corporatecomedians.com.au/main/index.php/comedians-105/melbourne-comedians/61-comedians/melbourne-comedians/185-doug-chappel |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-11-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161118164659/http://corporatecomedians.com.au/main/index.php/comedians-105/melbourne-comedians/61-comedians/melbourne-comedians/185-doug-chappel |archivedate=2016-11-18 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=April 12, 2016 |url=http://comedyunlimited.com.au/doug-chappel/ |title=Doug Chappel |publisher=Comedyunlimited.com.au |date=2016-04-12 |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref>
Doug Chappel has not been without his controversy and has been criticised in the past for his close association with many notorious underworld figures such as [[Mark "Chopper" Read]] and his comedy show tours with disgraced "AFL agent to the stars" [[Ricky Nixon]] which also included colourful 80's AFL star [[Warwick Capper]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ausstage.edu.au/pages/event/85672 |title=AusStage |publisher=AusStage |date= |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref><ref name="corporatecomedians1"/><ref>http://www.myfootyagent.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/myFootAgent-Sportsmans-Night-Package.pdf</ref>
Doug Chappel is also a passionate supporter of the Western Bulldogs AFL football team and has done numerous shows for them and many other AFL football clubs in the past. In 2016 Doug Chappel was the official comedian at the "Sons of the West" Grand Final Dinner with Western Bulldog premiership stars and captain [[Robert Murphy (footballer)|Robert Murphy]], [[Jake Stringer]], [[Marcus Bontempelli]] and club legends [[Doug Hawkins]] and [[Tony Liberatore]] to name a few.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/authenticautographs1/ |title=Authentic Autographs - Memorabilia & Fundraising Specialists |publisher=Facebook |date=2016-11-21 |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref>
Chappel released 2 CDs in [[2004 in music|2004]] titled ''The funniest man on the planet'' and ''The Footscray Rap'' in which he talks about his troubled past, the area in which he grew up and relationships.<ref name="digital1">[http://www.7digital.com/stores/sta/.../doug-chappel/the-funniest-man-on-the-planet/ ]{{dead link|date=December 2016}}</ref><ref name="amazon1">[https://www.amazon.co.uk/Footscray-Rap-Tracky-Dack.../B001GG6V8M ]{{dead link|date=December 2016}}</ref><ref name="digital1"/><ref name="amazon1"/>
